[[File:Tojjevvuk.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The madclaw Tojjevvuk]]
{{Quote|Our claws are tools, not weapons. To use them in battle is to become an animal. It is madness without honor.|translated=1|[[Zaalbar]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
'''Madclaw''' was a term used by the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]] of [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] to mark a dishonored member of their community.

Wookiee culture placed a high value on the use of their claws for peaceful, productive reasons only. Thus, any Wookiee who lashed out against another Wookiee, or any other living being, with their claws was deemed to be a madclaw. The title was a grave dishonor, since the Wookiees viewed the use of claws for anything other than tools as feral, and madclaws were usually sent into exile.

The Wookiees were not the only [[Species/Legends|species]] that believed in this philosophy. The [[Selkath/Legends|Selkath]] of [[Manaan/Legends|Manaan]] also had retractable claws and strictly forbade the use of them in battle.

==Famous madclaws==
{{Quote|"''Dishonorable''," they say! But is it really dishonorable or merely ''reasonable''? Look at them, look at these fine instruments nature gave us! And ''why''? To forever scratch tree bark with them? To pick an occasional morsel of food from between our fangs? You can't be ''serious''! These are meant for one thing and one thing only&mdash;for ''gut-spilling''!|translated=1|Tojjevvuk|<ref name="Chewbacca (2000) 1">[[Chewbacca (2000) 1|''Chewbacca'' (2000) 1]]</ref>}}
One of the few madclaws to become famous throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] was [[Zaalbar]], one of the companions of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Revan/Legends|Revan]]. He lashed out at his brother, [[Chuundar]], after discovering he'd been cutting deals with [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Corporation]] [[Slavery/Legends|slavers]]. His father, the chieftain [[Freyyr]], didn't believe him, and he was exiled. He was later pardoned after Chuundar's crimes were exposed.<ref name="KotOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>

The albino Wookiee [[Tojjevvuk]] also dishonored himself by using his claws to attack [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] when they fought over [[Mallatobuck/Legends|Mallatobuck]], but since that battle ended with Chewbacca hurling Tojjevvuk to his death in the [[Shadowlands/Legends|Shadowlands]], Tojjevvuk was never brought to justice by his people and formally dishonored with the title madclaw.<ref name="HttES" />

The Wookiee [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Snoova]] was deemed a madclaw for using his claws in his work and was rumored to have been originally forced to leave [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] for using his claws in a brawl over a paramour.<ref name="SotES">''[[Shadows of the Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref>

[[Reerookachuck]] was a Wookiee male taken from Kashyyyk as a slave at a young age and raised by [[Human/Legends|Human]] slaves, and had no interaction with other Wookiees until he was seventy. As such Reerookachuck did not learn that it was dishonorable for a Wookiee to use claws in combat.<ref name="BtDF">{{GamerCite|6|Bounties to Die For}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Fortunately, the West End Games folks also spotted the lapse and came to my rescue.|Timothy Zahn|<ref name="HE20">''[[Heir to the Empire: The 20th Anniversary Edition]]''</ref>}}
The concept of madclaws was, indirectly, created by [[Timothy Zahn]], author of "[[Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy|The Thrawn Trilogy]]." In his [[1991]] novel ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'', Zahn introduced the protractible claws of the Wookiees in order to make their tree-climbing more realistic. However, he realized that his new addition to canon caused a discrepancy: if the Wookiees indeed had claws, Chewbacca would have used them in the original ''[[Star Wars]]'' movies.<ref name="HE20" /> In the following year, ''[[Heir to the Empire Sourcebook]]'' resolved the discrepancy, explaining that it was a matter of honor that Wookiees never used their claws in combat, but kept them strictly for climbing.<ref name="HttES">''[[Heir to the Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref> 

In ''Star Wars'' [[canon]], a similar [[Wookiee honor code]] appears in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: A Junior Novel]]''.<ref name="TFA Junior Novel">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: A Junior Novel]]''</ref>

